# Library Functions

When editing `lib/functions/`, read the actual file for full signatures. This rule maps purpose to function.

## rhoai.sh — RHOAI installation and configuration

- **Channels**: get_rhoai_channel, get_available_rhoai_channels, select_rhoai_channel
- **Install**: install_rhoai_operator, install_rhoai_operator_interactive, initialize_rhoai
- **DSC**: create_datasciencecluster_v1 (2.x), create_datasciencecluster_v2 (3.x)
- **Config**: configure_rhoai_dashboard, create_gpu_hardware_profile, configure_gpu_resourceflavor, enable_user_workload_monitoring
- **MaaS/llm-d**: setup_llmd_infrastructure, setup_rhcl_for_llmd, deploy_llminferenceservice
- **Feast**: check_feast_operator, enable_feast_operator, deploy_banking_demo, diagnose_feature_store_interactive
- **MLflow**: enable_mlflow_operator
- **NVIDIA**: pin_nvidia_driver_version

## operators.sh — Operator lifecycle

- install_nfd_operator, install_gpu_operator, install_rhcl_operator, install_lws_operator, install_certmanager_operator, install_kueue_operator
- wait_for_authorino_service, configure_authorino_tls

## model-deployment.sh — Interactive model deployment wizard

- **Entry**: deploy_model_interactive (supports llm-d, vLLM Red Hat, vLLM Community, vLLM-Omni)
- Flow: runtime selection → model selection → namespace → resources/hardware profile → tool calling → auth → deploy
- Hardware profile annotations (all 3 required): hardware-profile-name, hardware-profile-namespace, hardware-profile-resource-version

## utils (lib/utils/)

- **os-compat.sh**: detect_os, grep_perl, base64_encode/decode, sed_inplace, calc_half, parse_memory_gi, timeout_cmd
- **rhoai-version.sh**: detect_rhoai_version, is_rhoai_33_or_higher, get_maas_endpoint, get_dashboard_url, is_llmd_available, list_deployed_models
- **common.sh**: apply_manifest, wait_for_resource, check_operator_installed, wait_for_operator_ready, ensure_namespace, approve_installplan
